snippet.textDisplay:
1) At 1 minute to the end of the game, under of 8 points, gentry put lonzo in. When he had plenty of occasion to put him early. Please, somebody explain to me the technical value of this move.

Don't tell me he was playing bad or losing too much balls because i dare you to find a player in the world that play intermittently like him and is in always in rhythm. FFS, how gentry manage lonzo's game time is inexplicable to me. And everytime he put him in a shitty team rotation, how is that possibile that he didn't understand yet: DON'T PUT HIM IN THE FRIKKING BENCH!!! but no, he HAS to use holiday instead... If you watch the famous games of nola's losing streak it is clear that there was no order, no hierarchy. Aforementioned losing streak ended since lonzo's played with regularity. This is not jinx, or macumba, or magic, is that the guy needs to stay on the court. The more he stay in the court the more the team can benefit from him and the team's skills will increase. How is that possible gentry still didn't get it?.. O_O whatever, maybe i don't understand or there's something i don't know. Probably both...


2) Putting togheter hart and reddick in the 4th quarter is just a weak move. The guys, no offense, but to me, are both shooters. Hart has dribbling and reddick is a better shooter but to me they are both shooter. Good in offense but they both lack in defense. And putting them both at the same time without any real defensive assets is just bananas. Beside lonzo and zion that was the 2nd team. I'm an nobody but if i had to really think about a team composition, i'd put 2 shooters at the same time when i'm under 10, or 20, anyway as a risky move, not when i'm even, vs this lakers.


3) I respect the fact that for the whole game holiday tried to guard lebron. Not blaming holiday, he did a terrific game and i think he did his best to lock the monster, but at this level i guess sometimes you just can't. It's ok, i get it, but at least don't faul him and give him 3 points play and the other teammates in the meantime should guard the other outside threats, so if lebron pass to team they can't shoot 3s (green, kcp...). Seems basic to me but i see this happening all the time that the shooters is completely free. If lebron score from inside it's only 2 points, if they score from outside is 3 points... guys..


This game was lost but it could be won by nola, so, overall good, but i didn't really liked some team-head's decisions :-/

For my cleansing this my plea,
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

Nothing but the blood of Jesus;

Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

Nothing but the blood of Jesus;
This is all my righteousness,
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

Now by this I’ll overcome—
Nothing but the blood of Jesus;
Now by this I’ll reach my home—
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

Nothing but the blood of Jesus,
All my praise for this I bring—
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.
